    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-26T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-26T12:00:00-05:00" n="1133"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1133">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00114A European War 1939/338: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-26T19:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 26, 1943—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 27—1:44 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>777. My 756, April 22, 4 p.m. Foreign Office states informally today that orders
                    will be issued in a few days for the release of all aviators who were interned
                    on March 26. This includes 20 Americans among them the two referred to in my
                    744, April 19,<note n="27" xml:id="d1133fn27">Not printed</note> who have since
                    been apprehended by the Turkish authorities.</p>
                <p>Please inform General Arnold.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
